  <prompt>
    Two-part task:
    1. **D-C-21 Activate `MatterMemoryService`**: the service exists in production
       (`src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Memory/MatterMemoryService.cs`) but is
       not wired into the chat-agent system prompt assembly. Wire it in via
       `PlaybookChatContextProvider` so cross-session same-matter conversations are
       coherent. **NOTE**: this task does NOT modify the service implementation — only
       activates it. Per spec FR-45.
    2. **D-C-22 Shared token budget tracker**: introduce
       `IPromptBudgetTracker` (or similar) that the factory + document context +
       knowledge retrieval + memory composition (task 067) all consume to share the 8K
       budget per NFR-10. Currently each subsystem consumes the budget independently —
       this tracker centralizes the accounting + emits telemetry on truncation events.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior AI platform engineer with familiarity with `MatterMemoryService` production
    code + `PlaybookChatContextProvider` prompt assembly.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `MatterMemoryService` activated; cross-session matter memory visible in agent
    prompts. Shared budget tracker introduced + consumed by all 4 subsystems; truncation
    telemetry emitted; 8K total budget enforced.
  </goal>

